caption: The best meal all weekend!  A fun atmosphere! Great hospitality!
This was truly one of the best tasting food establishments I had visited to date. Every mosol of food hit a pleasure center. You can tell the food was prepared with care. Also great table service.
Very Nice Vibe great authentic Italian foods great place to do business or just enjoy a nice meal by yourself or with a friend.
Great beer. Great pizza.

Have had good food/service pre covid but tried ordering delivery from here, kept getting delayed, and 2 hours later was told the order couldn’t be fulfilled? Couldn’t get in contact with anyone there and they never got back to us.
Terrible service. Do not go. The food is terrible.

Was looking for a good pizza in Baltimore and found it! This is a really neat place. Family friendly for lunch. First, menu is really good, plenty of choices. Order two different pizzas and both were delicious. They have a ton of draft beers. Interior decor is really cool, with a disco platform up a ladder and basically what looked to be the front of a car. Service was friendly and attentive. I wanted to buy one of their Pint classes and Manager (maybe owner?) was so accommodating and let us. This place was not really on our radar, but so glad we found it. I would return without hesitation. Lunch was great with teenagers. Had 80's and 90's music playing which Mom and Dad enjoyed. Highly recommend for lunch and even though we did not eat dinner, feel like dinner would be great also.
Fabulous prices on fabulous drinks.
Inattentive staff...carryout order took 48 minutes...and only 4 customers in the restaurant
Great food and reasonable prices

So I ordered from here via the Seamless service. Was sent a text confirmation and everything. Being that it was a weekend, and Valentine's day weekend at that, I wasn't surprised by the long wait time given to pick up. What did put me off was the process I had to go through attempting to cancel my order. First tried calling, only to get an answering service. No biggie, I figured, I'm in the area. I'll swing by and do it in person. Got there, was barely greeted by the hostess, had to practically wade through to get to the bar, just to be told (!) That "we don't use that delivery service". Bartender looked at me like I sprouted another head when I showed her that I received a confirmation text. A simple "sorry for the confusion" would've sufficed, but even that seemed like too much effort lol not impressed. Went to Fat tiger at the Broadway market, which was also packed, and got served quickly and professionally.
Great place to grab a quick drink after dinner.
Love the atmosphere! I come out for Karaoke night, it's a fun time after a long day at work!
decent meal, reasonably priced. definitely recommend the disco fries as an app!!
Great food great atmosphere
Food was fantastic and on time. Jaida was very hospitable. Great spot!
good bar food place. drinks are ok.
Charity was the best!!!!   She made us feel right at home.  She had amazing suggestions and just made our night so positive!  Thank you Charity
Fun restaurant, nice big tvs for sports, food was good and the service was great. Including a DJ with Disco ball, loved it.
Great happy hour choices and cool vibe!
Good food, great atmosphere, and quick, friendly service.
bad staff

Just went here for the first time for dinner. loved the decor and the vibe of the place; there was a DJ up above the restaurant in a little car. The food was delicious! I highly recommend the Carbonara pizza! We also had the cheesecake for dessert and it was amazing. The only reason I'm giving it 4 stars instead of 5 is because the music was so loud it was hard to talk at the table (we were s group of 7).
A little pricey but good food and beer, and a little outside area during nice weather.
Those Mozz' sticks tho 🤤 great beer selection on tap
My Roasted Salmon with Risotto, pears, salmoriglio wasn’t delicious. The atmosphere was amazing. Great music and good people. My first experience. I’m definitely coming back
Fun spot for lunch. Half a sandwich and delicious Asparagus leek soup for $9. Great deal, definitely plan to go back.
Cool spot,  good drinks
I wore my boogie nights costume for no reason. But all things considered they had a great selection t beers and food was on point

It's supposed to be Italian Pizza. It was burnt, fries weren't that great, waiter seemed unhappy with life and cared more for the bar customers. It was a light company lunch and we were 4 people who ordered 2 pizzas, gravy cheese fries, asparagus, bread sticks and drinks.....most likely won't go back. Please clean your pizza oven so the pizza isn't burnt. Oh and not a great idea where you put the music.....our waiter climbed a fire escape to some ledge where there was DJ equipment. Just not authentic. What's with the Irish pub theme? Makes no sense.
Waitress was very forgetful other than that it was a good place

Each dish we ordered was far too salty. We had the Lasagna, the Cacio e Pepe, Caesar Salad and Pepperoni Pizza. Every dish tasted nice, but with more salt than necessary. We were there on Friday night, Sep 20, 2019.
Pretty hard to review when you are rotting at the hostess stand. We finally left and went to Lebanese Taverna. Better choice actually.
Nice place 👌 very clean 👌 tasty 😋

Nice atmosphere, outdoor seating, stringed lights at night, nice design inside the restaurant, and the staff was nice. The menu was okay...(my daughter's and my own) food was much too peppery and not flavorful for my tastes. I'm unlikely to go back to dine here. Might be a good bar for those who partake.
Cool atmosphere, friendly staff, but the food is not great.
Great pizza, but so much more.  other food was great and reasonably priced.  Good location.

Good food and atmosphere. But the fact that on the days they are open until 2am, the kitchen closes at 12??? What sense does it make for a restaurant kitchen to close 2 hours in advance? Especially on a Friday night. At least have a late night menu that consists of finger food/appetizers.....I can understand an hour before closing . But 2 hours in advance????smh....
The food was so amazing I had to leave a review!! Absolutely superb food and service!
Good pizza and dj music

I'd driven past this place countless times and each time thought I'd like to try it someday. Friday was someday. The atmosphere is spot on and incredibly comfortable and welcoming. The service was top notch. The food... The food is absolutely delicious! I highly suggest giving Italian Disco a try. You will not be disappointed!

Nice atmosphere. Had a smokey vibe but that is because of the brick oven pizza. Great service despite the fact no one said what they're name. Great lunch menu although I didn't order anything off of it. Pizza was fresh, the grilled asparagus was awesome. Salmon alfredo was fresh. I wasn't disappointed. First time in and would definitely go again.
Good pizza
Ok.  Overpriced and not that delish.

Ok, first, we live in Hampden and our food came hot and ready to eat.  This place is awesome. Pizza is to die for; great chewy crust, prime toppings, excellent sauce. Meatballs are to die for. Top 3 of what we have had, possibly number 1. Simple tomatoe sauce on top is the kicker. Finally, half orders of pasta dishes. How many times have you been out and you both want pasta and pizza and it is too much food???? Well, this place allows for half orders of pasta. How awesome is that AND the pasta and pizza is perfect!  Al dente and great pizza. Thx Disco!!!!!
Awesome decor and good food. A little expensive.

We went here last week for lunch and we had such a nice time! Had a lovely waitress and the food was absolutely incredible. We got the bruschetta, meatballs, and fried mozzarella (which was THE best) everything came out fast and was fresh 😊 can’t ask for much more.
Upgrade from Bagby, its a great spot to watch sports games and enjoy an excellent pizza/Italian meal. Very cool vibe with the DJ booth that’s an old car

I walked in and ordered a chicken alfredo meal to go it was dry, salty, had practically no sauce and tasted like margarine on soggy noodles. After I called management to give feed back the manager was very incentive to the fact that I payed $20.00 for food that I was not going to eat past a taste. I'd  avoid this restaurant. A t.v. dinner chicken alfredo would have honestly been better.
Nice place but too dark inside. Prices are debatable.
Nice, cozy place. Went on a Monday night. Bartender was friendly. House made pasta. Ordered the pasta aribiatta. Warned it was spicy. It was! But not in a bad way. Would visit again.
Fabulous place! Will be back with the kids.

not great, not awful. i did not try the pizza as it appeared to be too much for me to eat during this visit, so maybe i will update this review if i decide to go a 2nd time.  anyway, i ordered the buffalo chicken sandwhich, with french fries (which costs $3 extra..... this will come in later). aside from taking 30+ minutes, with 8 staff (that i could see) serving the 10 customers (that i could see, 5 of which were sitting at the bar), the taste of the food was about what id expect from a corner deli. this plate, before tax, cost $16..... and i can think of a better way to spend $16 than at this place. the sandwhich was dressed to the 9's and piled so high that a fork & knife was necessary.... but the bun was obviously stale even before they toasted it, and the fries that i paid $3 extra for were covered in what appeared to be parm. and some greens..... but were cold and soppy (grease soppy.... because they're "hand cut" without being cooked fresh). additionally, the fries looked to be "whatever is left", judging by their size (we all know what the bottom of the chip bag looks like right?)  like i said.... maybe ill update this if i give it a 2nd go, but thats a BIG if.
Always love this spot.

Interesting concept (Italian restaurant with a disco ball and playing mostly 80s hits).  Pretty decent selection of beer.  Complimentary breadsticks seemed clones of Olive Garden breadsticks in appearance, crumb and taste.  Pizza was very good with very nice crust and well-seasoned sauce.  Also got a half-size serving of cacio e pepe, which was a little too al dente for my preference and too salty (although not to the point of being inedible).  Serving sizes are very generous.
A bit loud but tired a new drink and had a delicious pizza. Will go back again but with friends next time.

It is loud. It is fun. There is DJ way up above in an old Italian convertible. The food is good. We had pizza and spaghetti and meatballs. Both yum. They have a huge draft beer selection as well as prosecco on draft. Also yummy. This was our first visit and we will be back. Oh and you can dance too. Also food is reasonably priced for Harbor East.
Having a delicious Spinach salad with chicken. Good bartender, nice decor, will come back.

So for a place with name like that 2 things to be expected:  music and food.  I'll start with food. Food is surprisingly good as I was expecting basics and got carefully structured dishes with lots of flavor and character.  Appetizers were all on the spot and very good.  Meatballs I expected more.  But pasta was exceptional.  Too much salt, but texture and taste of a homemade pasta.  So the food is definately 4 stars.  Now on to music... Italian Disco or as many knew Italo Disco along with Eurodance run the world in 80's.  I was so looking forward to hearing that again.  But instead I got an ear full of some boring 70's/80's and even some current songs.  What a shame.  I seriously doubt that DJ even knows what is Italian Disco.  In fact, host had no clue and told me that they just play 70'/80's music.  So call it Oldies Disco and do not insult Italian. Music.   2 Stars for entertainment.  With that music place pretty much unsurprisingly cleared by 11:10pm on Saturday night.  Get real DJs that play real Italo and Euro Disco and you got something no other place has. Food is already there.  And for those that think the place is too loud, why don't you eat dinner at restaurant that does not have "Disco" in their name.   Dudh!

Not sure Italian food and disco music go together but the pizza and Italian apps are great. Get there for $10 pitchers of beer during happy hour and the best Mozzy stix you've had since you've been to ihop (believe me ihop has bangin Mozzy stix).
Fantastic addition to the Atlas Group family. Great service. Veal Parm is primo. Cocktail and beer selection unmatched. Go!!
Fun spot with good pizza
Best Roast Pork Sandwich this side of Philly (though it was skimpy on the hots).  If it's cold outside, bring your jacket; the restaurant was chilly and the marble table tops didn't help.
Decent food. Good service.
Good food. Amazing music. A happy place to be!!!  Great service. Fun drinks. All around good.
Love this place  I go there  once  a week
Really cute place..awesome live DJ..great food! Only reason for 4 instead of 5 stars: it's loud. Loved it though and will definitely return.
Great food and awesome atmosphere!
Good prices and great food.
I highly recommend the fried olives
Food was awesome!
The food was good the atmosphere was great definitely worth the tripķ
Cheesesteak is fantastic

They have one of the best portion-to-price happy hours in the city! Pictured are the meatballs, mozzarella sticks (far from ordinary!), and the Sloe Gin Fizz [Plymouth slow gin, Barr Hill gin, lemon juice, simple syrup, egg white, and prosecco]!

First time here was for their New Year’s Eve party which was FANTSTIC! This group of restaurants teamed up with their sister places The Elk Room and Tagliata for a night of great food, excellent drinks and three types of entertainment. Piano Bar sing-a-long at Tagliata’s, 3-piece Jazz trio at The Elk Room and a DJ at Italian Disco. We party-hopped, ate, drank, danced and sang until the party was over at 3am!! That was a big deal for my friends and I being in our mid-40’s. We can only stay out that late when we’re having fun and we were, all night long! It was worth every penny of the ticket price and fees. We hope this party happens again next year but in the meantime, we plan on coming back throughout the year to all 3 places. Thank you for a great time!!
Good pizza, fun atmosphere, great mussels.

The food is WAY oversalted. Even my salty snack loving kids complained that their lasagna was too salty. So were the spaghetti & meatballs. Pizza was mediocre and nothing to recommend; could have used more toppings. The music was super loud and we all had to raise our voices to be heard. If you want to eat salty overpriced Italian with Bon Jovi and 80s music blaring in the background, this is the place for you. The food at the old Bagby Pizza was much better, sadly.
Nice atmosphere and food was good but not great.  Pizza was very good
Good turkey meatballs

Little disappointed the second time around. Bartender spent most of his time on his cell phone. Sad to say, had a difficult time getting service, as he was clearly preoccupied. Spaghetti & turkey meatball dish was watery and not drained properly. This Italian dish could have been better.

Horrible service. Our waitress greeted us and then did not come back for 20 minutes to take our drink order. She kept trying to walk away while we were ordering, wasn't even busy. Music was so loud we had to scream to each other just to have a conversation. They had a 30 person party in the middle of the bar that they set up for during our dinner. The party arrived and was so loud and took over the back part of the restaurant. We were bumped into the entire time we ate by the staff and the party guests. Our table was never offered to be moved and no apology was issued. We were offered complimentary coffee but declined because we just wanted to get the heck out of there. Not worth the price at all and nothing like any of the other Atlas group restaurants.
Had a great time with my coworkers and VP. Great food and fun atmosphere.
The food here is overpriced for what it is. I would just go for drinks and maybe a pizza. Nothing was bad it just wasn't worth it at all.
Love this place, food was amazing
Good food. Good service. Incredibly loud after 8pm—if you want to have a conversation I would not recommend. The fried olives are nothing to write home about
My first time and I bit into a hard plastic in my calzone!

This is a casual place with nice atmosphere and friendly service. We sat at the bar and had a small pizza & breaded fried olives...nothing particularly remarkable but also no complaints, and I'd come back if I was in the area, although I wouldn't make a special trip - if I lived closer I could see myself coming more often since it isn't super expensive and It's like a friendly little neighborhood place. They also have a good selection of craft beers if you like that - I wanted to try a hard cider but they were out of it. We sat at the bar and talked with a guy who lived around the corner and was picking up carry out - he said he gets carry out regularly and he really loves the food here, so that's a good recommendation. It's primarily a younger crowd so it depends on what you're looking for. No frills and decent food - worth a visit if you're in the area.

This was the best dining experience near the harbor in a while. Love the music, the food and especially the service. Big shout out to our server, Keegan, who was attentive, witty and timely. Will be back soon.
We had a great time here tonight. Tony the bartender is awesome and it's a lovely place to chill and watch sports. the food is great and drinks will help you get tickets, lost or become a new parent.
Food flavor profile was good however it was a bit too salty.
The mussels were delicious but really need to be served with two or four pieces of bread if they're meant for sharing and the pizza special was solid.
I thought it was an actual disco so I was disappointed when I found out it was just a restaurant.  The food was good and the service was too.

My death's door meal used to live in Manhattan. Now, it's right down the street. The cacio e pepe with homemade bucatini is swoon worthy. I grew up with an Italian grandmother making this dish and it's almost impossible to find done well outside of Italy or NYC. Do yourself a favor and go hoover up a plate. You'll dream about it later. Cacio e pepe. Go. Get it. NOW
This place rocks on a Saturday night!! Whoever the DJ was on Sat Aug 25th 2018 needed a stern raise!!
Good place for lunch, the subs and pizza are nice.
Best pizza in Maryland

Easy to get seated on Saturday night at 7pm.  Waitress was very friendly.  Ordered the meatballs which were amazing.  Antipasto salad was great and the lasagne delicious.  Beer selection was amble and the mixed drink great.  Finished with a cannoli for dessert.  I’d definitely come back.

Chicken was super bland. I thought it was just me but the lady I was with said the same thing about hers and her mozzarella and tomato salad was sad.   Salads for $18 each and they weren’t enjoyable at all. Bring back Bagbys!
Great pizza! Meatballs were delicious and the bartender was super!
I don't think there's a word to describe the food!! All homemade and everything I ate was omg delicious!! Over 30 draft beers ready to go!! Little Italy has a rising star!!

I've had two great meals and drinks at Italian Disco over the past couple of weeks.  The staff is friendly and professional and the decor and vibe are quite unique for Baltimore.  And the outdoor seating is in an amazing hidden courtyard in Harbor East.  We will be back.

I'm surprised nobody has commented on the outrageous and non-standard beer prices. Most glasses are 9-12 bucks. Not for rare or exceptional stuff. One of the most mass-produced wheat beers is $12 a glass. Local pale ales and single IPAs are $10 a glass. Can be found anywhere else for half that.
Grabbed a to go Steak and Cheese sub with a co-worker. Tasted great. Plenty of fresh meat and cheese. Place looks awesome inside. We can't wait to come for a sit down lunch or after work drink!
